ven 40. You may find folks in their 50s on this board with stuff like yours.<br><br>Like the rest of the peanut gallery, I agree, that you should start saving for a haste item.<br><br>Range slot: get a bow (smooth ashwood with silk thread has reasonable damage and low delay) for pulling. And a goranga idol for the times you are not pulling (they seem to be about 500-800p on my server). You may as well retire the bow when you get your archery to 75 (class limit).<br><br>2hb: pick up something to practice with while waiting for a spot in a group. Glowing wooden crooks are cheap and plentiful. When you get to the high end of the game, some wonderful 2hb may come your way, and nothing is worse than getting a great weapon and having zero skill in it. <p><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64195'>Combat Profile</a><br><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64207'>Tradeskill Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalyawanderfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valya Wanderfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 855<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/29/02 6:38:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.pacbell.net/skfitz/valface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipment Suggestions please</span><hr size=1> I agree with the above posters and I love the Glowing Wooden Crook idea, I wielded one for a while to practice with, it was very funny. <p><font size="+1">	<a href="http://www.geocities.com/valya_w" target="_blank"><b><u>Valya Wanderfoot </u></b></a>, </font><br>60 Crusader<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=94293">Magelo Profile</a><br>Melliasan Sforzanda, 41 Bard